<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - FULLER 10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS - INSTALL - SHIFT BAR
        HOUSING
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>SHIFT BAR HOUSING</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean the gasket mounting surface of the main case and shift bar housing, and place a new
                gasket on the main case.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the shift bar housing shift shaft in the neutral position so the yokes will be
                positioned to fit over the mainshaft sliding clutches.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">In the main case of the transmission, place mainshaft sliding clutches in their neutral
                position.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide the auxiliary section range piston bar forward or rearward to align the notch in the
                piston bar with the notch in the range yoke bar (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13032g7">Figure 167</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With all parts properly aligned, lower the shift bar housing straight down into position (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13032g7">Figure 167</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply Loctite 242 or equivalent to the retaining bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the 16 retaining bolts. Tighten the bolts to 54 to 61 Nm (40 to 45 ft-lbs) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13032g8">Figure 168</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13032g7" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G13032g7.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 167. Install Shift Bar Housing</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f13032g8" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G13032g8.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 168. Install Retaining Bolts</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
